shot with people who

808
00:47:39,000 --> 00:47:41,200
actually are in the same room.

809
00:47:41,200 --> 00:47:43,033
And one interesting
note about that

810
00:47:43,033 --> 00:47:47,400
is that when we shot the film,
we use this special device so

811
00:47:47,400 --> 00:47:50,934
that we couldn't use
actual phone lines,

812
00:47:50,934 --> 00:47:55,200
but we had the characters on
phones, never in the same room.

813
00:47:55,200 --> 00:47:57,600
So as much as
possible, we simulated

814
00:47:57,600 --> 00:48:01,033
the world of phone sex as
it existed at that time.

815
00:48:07,967 --> 00:48:10,700
When you make a short
film, basically everyone

816
00:48:10,700 --> 00:48:13,633
has to work for free, and
you're pulling in every favor

817
00:48:13,633 --> 00:48:15,200
that you can and
you're asking people

818
00:48:15,200 --> 00:48:17,533
to extend themselves
on their own time,

819
00:48:17,533 --> 00:48:19,633
and I was a little
uncomfortable with that.

820
00:48:19,633 --> 00:48:22,300
I wasn't such a good asker.

821
00:48:22,300 --> 00:48:24,567
And at the same
time, I had a career

822
00:48:24,567 --> 00:48:27,633
previously as an
activist for human rights

823
00:48:27,633 --> 00:48:29,033
and the environment.

824
00:48:29,033 --> 00:48:31,734
And so I came up with
the idea of creating

825
00:48:31,734 --> 00:48:37,133
the film as a fundraiser for
the Minority AIDS Project.

826
00:48:37,133 --> 00:48:38,867
And this was a
little bit strange.

827
00:48:38,867 --> 00:48:40,333
It had never been done before.

828
00:48:40,333 --> 00:48:42,700
And there was a real good
reason why it hadn't been done,

829
00:48:42,700 --> 00:48:45,700
and that is that there
was no market, really,

830
00:48:45,700 --> 00:48:46,967
