00:53:42,133 --> 00:53:45,166
He said something like,
I know where you live.

945
00:53:45,166 --> 00:53:47,400
I'm going to come there.

946
00:53:47,400 --> 00:53:50,300
And in the moment, Helen,
great actress that she is,

947
00:53:50,300 --> 00:53:53,600
just completely jumped and
gave the perfect reaction.

948
00:53:53,600 --> 00:53:55,867
And then the only
thing left was to see

949
00:53:55,867 --> 00:53:57,900
was she going to be
upset with me afterwards

950
00:53:57,900 --> 00:53:59,834
because of that manipulation?

951
00:53:59,834 --> 00:54:02,300
So we said cut and
there was a pause,

952
00:54:02,300 --> 00:54:03,867
and I'm kind of sweating it out.

953
00:54:03,867 --> 00:54:06,200
She just turned, cool
as a cucumber to Tony

954
00:54:06,200 --> 00:54:08,233
and said, great scene, Tony.

955
00:54:08,233 --> 00:54:10,633
And never spoke of
it again, and I never

956
00:54:10,633 --> 00:54:12,934
checked up about it with her.

957
00:54:12,934 --> 00:54:15,700
So to this day, I don't know
whether she knew what we did

958
00:54:15,700 --> 00:54:19,033
or if she was just so in it,
it didn't even occur to her

959
00:54:19,033 --> 00:54:22,734
that anything was different.

960
00:54:22,734 --> 00:54:26,500
One of the final things we did
on the film was the soundstage,

961
00:54:26,500 --> 00:54:32,834
the post-production, and the
key pieces where the music--

962
00:54:32,834 --> 00:54:34,333
there's a lot of
music in this film.

963
00:54:34,333 --> 00:54:35,767
It was really important to me.

964
00:54:35,767 --> 00:54:38,633
And the song that
had to be in there,

965
00:54:38,633 --> 00:54:41,367
as far as I was concerned,
