966
00:54:41,367 --> 00:54:44,800
the Marvin Gaye song, title
of our film, of course.

967
00:54:44,800 --> 00:54:48,200
And we had tried really hard
to get the rights to the song

968
00:54:48,200 --> 00:54:49,633
and we hadn't heard back.

969
00:54:49,633 --> 00:54:52,467
It wasn't a no, we just
didn't hear anything.

970
00:54:52,467 --> 00:54:55,100
And now there was
no time left, and I

971
00:54:55,100 --> 00:54:56,467
knew someone who
knew someone who

972
00:54:56,467 --> 00:54:59,100
knew someone who got in
touch with EMI and said,

973
00:54:59,100 --> 00:55:00,633
what's going on?

974
00:55:00,633 --> 00:55:03,967
And what we found out was is
that the estate of Marvin Gaye

975
00:55:03,967 --> 00:55:07,567
had given us the rights to
the song weeks and weeks ago,

976
00:55:07,567 --> 00:55:11,033
but there was a co-writer
who they couldn't find,

977
00:55:11,033 --> 00:55:13,900
and therefore they
couldn't get his approval.

978
00:55:13,900 --> 00:55:15,867
So they said, the only
way you can use the song

979
00:55:15,867 --> 00:55:19,300
is if you write a letter,
little guy that you are,

980
00:55:19,300 --> 00:55:23,533
indemnifying multibillion
dollar conglomerate EMI

981
00:55:23,533 --> 00:55:27,700
against any possible future
claims from this co-writer.

982
00:55:27,700 --> 00:55:30,033
So I talked to my
lawyer, while I

983
00:55:30,033 --> 00:55:31,500
was right there on
the sound stage,

984
00:55:31,500 --> 00:55:32,934
and my lawyer said, don't do it.

985
00:55:32,934 --> 00:55:34,100
Don't do it.

986
00:55:34,100 --> 00:55:37,734
And I thought, whoever this
guy is, if he ever turns up,

987
00:55:37,734 --> 00:55:40,367
he's got to know
it's a benefit film.

988
00:55:40,367 --> 00:55:44,367
It's helping people, and he's
not going to create a problem.

989
00:55:44,367 --> 00:55:48,100
So I decided to go for it, and
20 years later, I have never

990
00:55:48,100 --> 00:55:52,567
heard anything from he or
his people, and if I ever do,

991
00:55:52,567 --> 00:55:56,433
I'm still hopeful and confident
that everything will be fine.

992
00:55:56,433 --> 00:55:58,333
But that was probably
the biggest risk

993
00:55:58,333 --> 00:56:02,333
that I had to take as
a young filmmaker, just

994
00:56:02,333 --> 00:56:06,133
to protect the quality of what
it was I was trying to create.

995
00:56:13,900 --> 00:56:17,233
In order to do the film
with a very small budget,

996
00:56:17,233 --> 00:56:19,567
we decided half the money
would go towards production

997
00:56:19,567 --> 00:56:22,367
and half the money would
go towards post-production.

998
00:56:22,367 --> 00:56:26,967
But also, as somebody who was
the writer, producer, director,

999
00:56:26,967 --> 00:56:31,233
