1013
00:57:09,233 --> 00:57:12,066
We'll finish the
shoot and then we'll

1014
00:57:12,066 --> 00:57:17,800
see if we can get donations
of editing bays and everything

1015
00:57:17,800 --> 00:57:20,200
else we needed to create
a rough cut of the film

1016
00:57:20,200 --> 00:57:22,100
that then we could market.

1017
00:57:22,100 --> 00:57:24,767
So that's what we
ended up having to do.

1018
00:57:24,767 --> 00:57:29,900
We got to a good cut
of the film and used

1019
00:57:29,900 --> 00:57:33,567
temporary sound, nothing
that we paid for, et cetera,

1020
00:57:33,567 --> 00:57:37,266
and took it to the one place
that was on the top of my list

1021
00:57:37,266 --> 00:57:40,600
that I thought would want
it, and that was Showtime.

1022
00:57:40,600 --> 00:57:43,100
And Showtime took one
look at the film, who

1023
00:57:43,100 --> 00:57:47,100
was in it, the subject matter,
and they said, yes, absolutely.

1024
00:57:47,100 --> 00:57:48,367
We'll do it.

1025
00:57:48,367 --> 00:57:50,200
So I was really thrilled
that the whole idea

1026
00:57:50,200 --> 00:57:51,867
was coming together,
not just as a film,

1027
00:57:51,867 --> 00:57:53,967
but as a benefit as well.

1028
00:57:53,967 --> 00:57:55,967
And what Showtime
and I worked out

1029
00:57:55,967 --> 00:57:59,100
was that as a part of
their deal with me,

1030
00:57:59,100 --> 00:58:02,533
which was just going to
recoup all of my costs--

1031
00:58:02,533 --> 00:58:04,834
so I wasn't making any
money in the process--

1032
00:58:04,834 --> 00:58:08,100
but they would give
